{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014pVUWfovKgPXCf7az5HEGP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me provide you with the complete summary:\n\n## Exploration Report: anchor-client Package\n\n### 1. Full Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/\n├── eslint.config.js\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n└── src/\n    ├── index.ts\n    ├── coinflip.ts         (type definition file)\n    ├── coinflip.json       (runtime IDL JSON)\n    ├── platform.ts         (type definition file)\n    └── platform.json       (runtime IDL JSON)\n```\n\n### 2. package.json\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/package.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"types\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"exports\": {\n    \".\": \"./src/index.ts\"\n  },\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"eslint . --fix\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest --passWithNoTests\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@coral-xyz/anchor\": \"^0.32.1\",\n    \"@solana/web3.js\": \"^1.98.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@rng-utopia/config\": \"workspace:*\",\n    \"@types/node\": \"^22.10.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.7.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points**:\n- ESM module with TypeScript as the source\n- Anchor 0.32.1 (matches your dev environment)\n- No build output — it's a pure TypeScript/types package\n- Main export is `./src/index.ts`\n\n### 3. src/index.ts\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts`\n\n```typescript\n// IDL JSON (runtime values)\nimport CoinflipIDL from \"./coinflip.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport PlatformIDL from \"./platform.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\n\n// Type-safe IDL types (compile-time)\nexport type { Coinflip } from \"./coinflip.js\";\nexport type { Platform } from \"./platform.js\";\n\n// Re-export IDLs as typed constants\nexport { CoinflipIDL, PlatformIDL };\n```\n\n**Pattern**:\n- Imports IDL JSON files with `with { type: \"json\" }` (JSON module import syntax)\n- Exports TypeScript type definitions from `.ts` files\n- Re-exports the JSON IDLs as runtime constants\n- This is the **canonical pattern for typed program interfaces**\n\n### 4. IDL/Program Exports\n\n**Coinflip Program**:\n- **Type file**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.ts`\n- **IDL JSON**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json`\n- **Address**: `BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx`\n- **Version**: 0.1.0\n\n**Platform Program**:\n- **Type file**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/platform.ts`\n- **IDL JSON**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/platform.json`\n- **Address**: `85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA`\n- **Version**: 0.1.0\n\n### 5. Pattern for Typed Program Interfaces\n\nThe anchor-client uses a **dual-layer pattern**:\n\n**Layer 1: Type Definition (.ts)**\n- `coinflip.ts` and `platform.ts` contain **exported type definitions** named `Coinflip` and `Platform`\n- These types are **hand-written** from the source-of-truth IDL\n- They define all instructions, accounts, errors, and types in camelCase for JavaScript/TypeScript\n- Example structure:\n  ```typescript\n  export type Coinflip = {\n    \"address\": \"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\",\n    \"metadata\": { \"name\": \"coinflip\", \"version\": \"0.1.0\", \"spec\": \"0.1.0\" },\n    \"instructions\": [ ... ],\n    \"accounts\": [ ... ],\n    \"events\": [ ... ],\n    \"errors\": [ ... ],\n    \"types\": [ ... ]\n  }\n  ```\n\n**Layer 2: Runtime IDL (.json)**\n- `coinflip.json` and `platform.json` are the **actual IDL JSON files**\n- Imported with the JSON module syntax: `import IDL from \"./file.json\" with { type: \"json\" }`\n- Used at runtime by Anchor clients to construct program instances\n- Snake_case naming in the JSON (e.g., `cancel_match`, `coinflip_match`)\n\n**Index.ts Export Pattern**:\n```typescript\n// Type-safe at compile time\nexport type { Coinflip, Platform };\n\n// Runtime values\nexport { CoinflipIDL, PlatformIDL };\n```\n\nThis allows consumers to:\n- Use the types for TypeScript safety: `const program = new Program<Coinflip>(CoinflipIDL, ...)`\n- Pass the IDL objects to Anchor's Program constructor\n- Get full IDE autocomplete and type checking\n\n### Key Observations\n\n1. **No code generation** — The types are hand-maintained alongside the JSON IDLs (though they should mirror `target/idl/` in the Anchor programs)\n2. **Convention mismatch** — JSON uses snake_case (`cancel_match`), type file uses camelCase (`cancelMatch`)\n3. **Central export** — `index.ts` is the single entry point for all program interfaces\n4. **Read-only in contributor workflow** — Per your CLAUDE.md, `packages/anchor-client/` is off-limits; changes come from auto-generated IDLs\n\nAll files are located in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/` and follow ESM + TypeScript conventions with no build step required."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abfa92b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 43531\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 26950</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d859bc11-91b4-4b69-a88e-12eb400e4b26","uuid":"88ef6652-249e-4c9c-9a70-37671ce40c72","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the anchor-client package at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/`. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory structure\n2. The contents of `package.json`\n3. The contents of `src/index.ts`\n4. How