{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01974fwmUwusuQcTUoxqZiSj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now update `browser.ts` — the browser entry point doesn't include Buffer-dependent functions. The lord functions use `Buffer` in PDA derivation (`getRoundPda`, `getConfigPda`), so those should NOT be exported from browser.ts. But `mapSlotToPlayer` and `determineWinnerFromRandomness` use `DataView` which is browser-safe. Let me check — actually `determineWinnerFromRandomness` in lordofrngs doesn't use Buffer, it uses `DataView`. But it calls `mapSlotToPlayer` which is also Buffer-free. The PDA functions use `Buffer`. So I should export the non-PDA functions from browser.ts.\n\nActually, looking at the browser.ts pattern more closely — it doesn't export ANY coinflip functions at all (no `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID`, no `getMatchPda`, etc.). So I should follow the same pattern and not export lord functions from browser.ts. The browser export is only for types and non-blockchain utilities.\n\nLet me not add anything to browser.ts — it doesn't export any game-specific client code."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":540,"cache_read_input_tokens":63112,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":540},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d859bc11-91b4-4b69-a88e-12eb400e4b26","uuid":"6d882fc7-a01c-4acb-8664-c85ec02ececd"}
